Day 11 â€“ ES6+ Modern JavaScript

Today's Focus: Arrow Functions, Template Literals, Destructuring
What I Learned: Modern JavaScript features for cleaner code. Learned:

Arrow functions syntax: () => {}

Template literals with ${variables}

Destructuring arrays and objects

Spread operator ...

Default parameters

Import/export modules

Practice Example: Modern Syntax
// Arrow function
const multiply = (a, b) => a * b;

// Template literal
const greet = name => `Hello, ${name}!`;

// Destructuring
const user = {name: 'John', age: 25};
const {name, age} = user;

// Spread operator
const arr1 = [1, 2, 3];
const arr2 = [...arr1, 4, 5];

Practice Questions:

Convert all regular functions to arrow functions

Use template literals for dynamic HTML generation

Destructure data from API response object
